               </table>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div subtype="1" type="letter">
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1841-01-29">January 29th 1841</date>
               </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>This day we the undersigners have proceeded to value the real estate of Walter Bell  <choice>
                  <abbr>Dec'd</abbr>
                  <expan>Deceased</expan>
               </choice> and do assess the value thereof to Seventeen Hundred Dollars together with the former valuation done by us on the <date when="1840-06-05">5th of June 1840</date> of the perishable property <del type="overstrike">
                  <unclear/>
               </del> Walter Bell <choice>
                  <abbr>Dec'd</abbr>
                  <expan>Deceased</expan>
               </choice> of  Thirteen Hundred and Sixty three Dollars 55 cents making in the whole three Thousand Sixty three 55 cents to the which valuation to the best of our knowledge <lb/> we sign our names and affix our seals <lb/> day and date above written</p>
            <signed>
               <name type="person">A Caldwell</name>
               <add place="right of signature">
                  <figure>
                     <figDesc>seal</figDesc>
                  </figure>
               </add>
            </signed>
            <signed>
               <name type="person">Gilford Mills</name>
               <add place="right of signature">
                  <figure>
                     <figDesc>seal</figDesc>
                  </figure>
               </add>
            </signed>
            <signed>
               <name type="person">W. T. Reynolds</name>
               <add place="right of signature">
                  <figure>
                     <figDesc>seal</figDesc>
                  </figure>
               </add>
            </signed>
         </div>
